block.name: mif_baaw

register.name: MIF_BAAW_START0
register.comment: 26 MSbits for the 36-bit address corresponding to the start of range 0(WLBT CPU programmer's view). The top 26 bits are valid. Other bits are ignored.

register.name: MIF_BAAW_END0
register.comment: 26 MSbits for the 36-bit address corresponding to the end of range 0(WLBT CPU programmer's view). The top 26 bits are valid. Other bits are ignored. This is the last byte of the region being remapped.

register.name: MIF_BAAW_REMAP0
register.comment: 26 MSbits for the 36-bit address corresponding to the start of the range 0(AP CPU programmer's view)

register.name: MIF_BAAW_REMAP1

register.name: MIF_BAAW_REMAP2
register.comment: 26 MSbits for the 36-bit address corresponding to the start of the range 2(AP CPU programmer's view). The top 26 bits are valid. Other bits are ignored.

register.name: MIF_BAAW_START3
register.comment: 26 MSbits for the 36-bit address corresponding to the start of range 3(WLBT CPU programmer's view). The top 26 bits are valid. Other bits are ignored.

register.name: MIF_BAAW_REMAP3

register.name: MIF_BAAW_START4
